the third world can reduce the number of its 
poor to 800 million from todays 11 billion if the right policies 
are followed over the next decade according to world bank 
president barber conable 
about one person in four among third world countries can be 
considered poor but the ranks of the poor could be cut by nearly a 
third by means of strict economic and social reforms conable said 
developed nations also should increase aid to their poorer 
neighbors he added 
strategy to reduce poverty should be one of the international 
communitys fundamental objectives in the 1990s he told 
reporters in advance of the release sunday of the banks annual 
world development report 
the 1990 issue is devoted to the problem of easing poverty 
which conable said is the banks main purpose owned by 151 
countries the bank is the biggest source of aid to the third 
world lending more than 20 billion a year 
the world bank says anyone is poor if he or she earns less than 
370 a year by that standard the average person in 25 countries is 
