business he also wants them to contain inflation get rid of 
unnecessary public spending and allow realistic prices for farm 
products foreign currency imports and exports he wants them to 
hold down deficits in their budgets and their balance of 
international payments 
some third world leaders are reluctant to follow such policies 
on the ground that they make life more difficult for poor people in 
the short run 
michel camdessus head of the international monetary fund the 
banks sister organization said in a recent speech how do the 
poor who have little or no assets fare when runaway inflation is 
set loose by easy money policies when factories close down because 
of overvalued exchange rates when there is no incentive to produce 
crops because state monopolies pay prices that do not cover the 
cost of production 
camdessus said the poor are the first hit the worst hit the 
least able to protect themselves 
both conable and camdessus also urge the importance of safety 
nets to protect the poorest people from the rising prices that may 
result from the new policies 
conable proposed a twopronged strategy against poverty 
emphasis on the use of labor the third worlds most abundant 
asset to be mobilized by the incentives of the market and 
emphasis on providing health care and education 
he said parts of the strategy had been tried successfully in 
countries as different as colombia and indonesia chile and 
