muster to keep the party alive 
the partys national committee had voted 175 on june 3 to 
suspend its constitution and disband 
at the time owen cited the partys declining membership which 
had collapsed to 6200 from a peak of 68000 soon after the social 
democrats were founded in january 1981 
owen is one of only three legislators the party has in the 
650member house of commons the three will continue to hold their 
seats as independent social democrats 
owens decision to pull out was seen as the end of the party 
but martin said he would ask the partys parliamentary candidates 
to remain on board to prepare for the next election which must be 
held by mid1992 
owen and three other former cabinet ministers broke with the 
labor party in 1981 to offer voters a centrist alternative to the 
conservative party and thenincreasingly leftist laborites 
the social democrats had hoped to supplant labor as the main 
challenger to the conservatives who are led by prime minister 
margaret thatcher 
but labor led by neil kinnock has abandoned its support for 
unilateral nuclear disarmament and unveiled a more centrist 
platform this year recent polls show it leads the conservatives 
 
the social democrats enjoyed their biggest electoral success 
when they joined with the longerestablished liberals under the 
name alliance that group polled 26 percent of the national vote in 
the 1983 general election and 226 percent in 1987 
but because of britains winnertakeall electoral system it 
never won more than a handful of parliamentary seats 
after winning only 22 of the 650 parliamentary districts in 
1987 a majority of the membership of the two parties agreed to 
merge as the social and liberal democrats 
owen and loyal supporters opposed to the merger remaining 
social democrats 
last month owen said he had no plans for now to rejoin the 
labor party he served as foreign minister from 197779 under a 
labor government and was once seen as a potential prime minister 
